The global Polyethylene Terephthalate (PET) bottle market is segmented based on product type, neck type, end-user industry, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, the market is divided into amorphous PET and crystalline PET. Amorphous PET bottles are commonly used for beverages and food packaging due to their transparent nature, while crystalline PET bottles are preferred for products requiring more rigidity such as household cleaning agents and personal care items. When it comes to neck type, options include ROPP/BPV, standard, and wide mouth, catering to the diverse needs of different industries. In the end-user industry segment, the market serves food & beverages, pharmaceuticals, personal care & cosmetics, household care, and others. Additionally, the distribution channel segment includes both online and offline channels to reach consumers effectively.

